She always said I was “chosen”…
I was adopted by this special women right around this time in 1968…
Happy heavenly Mother’s Day! Could have used you to heal me through some struggles the last few years - I love you and miss you and I am so grateful for all that you did to make me feel loved and supported

My time at FOX which I am so grateful for!

Never good bye..just see you soon..
Thank you to everyone that has reached out to me with kindness and support!
After an amazing 32+ year run at FOX 11, I have decided to step away. Words cannot express the gratitude I have for the opportunity and experiences that KTTV gave me over the last three decades. This company helped me raise my family- Now it’s time for a pause to spend much needed time with my family and friends.

I started my career as a college intern and was fortunate enough to be hired as a news assistant in 1990. From there I helped launch the FOX 11 morning news and Good Day L.A. as the weather and traffic producer. On-air weekend weather, SkyFox helicopter reporting and then the evening weather followed. Although challenging at times, each of these paths were filled with some of the  best times of my life with the greatest news professionals in Los Angeles. What an incredible privilege it was to work my entire professional career on one team. God I will miss playing second base, DH-ing or being called out of the bull pen with my teammates always trying to get in the win column and be the best..

Thank you to all of my colleagues..my FRIENDS..who made playing at “work” so easy and enjoyable. You all helped me grow professionally and personally and have been family to me. You are by far the most talented and hard working crew out there. I will miss YOU all deeply and wish you continued success with your dedication to covering our city…from the pursuits to heavy precipitation and every story in between. 

Most importantly, I want to sincerely thank all of our wonderful and supportive viewers..our “customers”as one manager taught me..who let me come into their homes and share my passion for our dynamic city, atmosphere and ocean…My cloud watching, surf reports and sunset alerts are not over yet..From the slopes to the shore…stay tuned here and on my twitter @RickDickertWX for more weather updates and knowledge! Be well and love to everyone-Time is free..but it is priceless..RD

Thank you @adriandacosta68 for bringing us together! Great time at @etsurfboards @ddel2 - great to see you @gregsworld and your help with our surf culture- @dane.acosta you are so talented! @dornvince and @dane_mack what stories we shared!! Love you guys
The LOVE of my life - She has given  me so much care and admiration - I love you deeply Stephanie Rae ❤️❤️
